race.comment: SAVAGE DANCER (9) was a savage drifter in betting first-up but looked the winner midway down the Belmont straight before her fitness gave way. Better for that run and out to 1200m now is a big tick. Pike rides from a much better barrier and she looks set to go one better. AWESOME BOY (1) resumes here without a trial, but he showed good ability in his 3YO campaign which saw him start a $10 chance at Listed level. Can be positive from the draw and he'll give a bold sight if he's fit enough. HARD SOLO (10) bolted in two back at Geraldton and took on the Belgravia last time out where she wasn't disgraced. Down in the weights again today and she has the speed to offset the sticky barrier. Can put her best foot forward. GOLD FLAKES (2) got back to winning ways last time out and can build on that performance. ALASKALOT (3) hasn't been to the races since 2023, though showed promising signs in his recent trial. Any market moves have to be respected.
